Description
-----------

The breadcrumb trail tag is used for displaying the hierarchy of the
current page. It can be fully customized by changing the parameters:

* The Tag/BreadcrumbTrail:omitLast parameter can be used to always omit
  the last path component in the trail (which is normally the page
  itself).

* The Tag/BreadcrumbTrail:omitIndexFile parameter can be used to omit
  the last path component if it is an index file for a directory (see
  File/DirectoryHandler for more information about index files). This
  behaviour can be overridden for individual index files by setting the
  meta information `omitIndexFileInBreadcrumbTrail`.


